Reply to support tickets in your Customer Area

You can now reply to support tickets without leaving your Adyen Customer Area, making it easier to manage your support interactions in one place. **Benefits:** - All-in-one support - Faster, smarter support - Track your tickets - Save time **Get started** Log into your Adyen Customer Area account.

Stay ahead of card scheme thresholds with our new dashboard

We’ve added a Card Monitoring Program dashboard to the Risk & Disputes Insights Page to help you track dispute ratios and avoid compliance issues before they happen. ### Benefits - Monitor card program status in real time - Reduce risk and avoid penalties with early insights ### Get started Log in to your Customer Area and head to Insights > Risk & Disputes > Card Monitoring Programs. You’ll find all the data you need in one place. Please note that this dashboard is only accessible at Company level, not merchant level.

Apple Pay is now available for all browsers on Mac, PC and beyond

With our latest update, shoppers can pay using Apple Pay on any browser, boosting conversion rates and streamlining checkout. ### Benefits - Reach more shoppers, drive more volume - Built-in security and SCA compliance ### Get started To activate Apple Pay on all browsers, upgrade to Web Drop-in/Components v6.11.0. Check out our documentation for full instructions.

Smarter fraud decisions, made visible

See exactly how our machine learning models assess fraud risk. Get insights into the signals behind each decision so you can act with more confidence and control. ### Benefits - Understand the why behind every fraud block - Make more informed decision ### Get started To access the signals, go to any card based payment that was fraud disputable (e.g. a Mastercard payment). You can do so via the **Customer Area** > **Transactions** > **Payments** > Select a payment and click on the **Risk score**.
